Design patterns
- represent some of the best practices adapted by experienced OO sw developers
- systematically name, motivate, explain a general design
to address a recurring design problem in OO system

3 types
1. Creational
About class instantiation or object creation
Class instantiation uses inheritance effectively
Object creation uses delegation effectively
E.g Factory, Builder, Singleton, Object pool, Prototype

2. Structural
About organizing different classes and objects to form larger structures and provide new functionality
E.g Adapter, Bridge, Composite, Decorator

3. Behavioral
About identifying common communication patterns btw objects and realize these patterns
E.g Chain of responsibility, Command, Interpreter, Mediator

